@body
Plans of the highest priority are listed first.
<p>
<ul>
<li>Search gtags.conf in the directory specifyed by --sysconfdir too.
<li>Delete intrusive bindings for mouse. (gtags.el)
<li>Detecting and ignoring recursive symbolic links. (gtags)
<li>Support of tag stack per window. Currently tag stack is only one per emacs. (gtags.el)
<li>Pickup definitions of data type, enum name, enum value, struct member name,
	union name and struct name in C language.
	Finally, remove GSYMS. (gtags-parser, gtags)
<li>Rewrite the CGI program using C language instead of Perl.
<li>Support of glob pattern for path name search (global -P).
<li>Rewrite gtags-parser(1) using flex(1) completely.
<li>Plug-in parser (shared library) for htags(1).
<li>Support of new languages.
	Here is a list of candidates:
        <ul>
	<li>lex
	<li>ruby
	<li>python
	<li>perl
	<li>scheme
	<li>C#
        </ul>
<li>Rewrite function header using Doxygen style.
<li>The --dynamic option generates not only index pages but also source code pages.
<li>Support of gtags-query-replace (gtags.el).
<li>Visual interface using GUI.
<li>Ttags(1) command.<br>
        Ttags(1) is similar to htags(1) but generates a TeX source for a book
        instead of a hypertext.
<li>Allow spaces in path name of source files.
<li>Support of multi-bytes code set.
<li>Support of tag type. (like Exuberant Ctags.)
</ul>
Any contributions are appreciated.
Please see <a href=contribute.html>contribution</a>.
